    <fr:title text="Selective ordered semirings">Selective ordered semirings</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>An <html:em>ordered semiring</html:em> is a set with two monoid structures: an
idempotent, commutative <html:em>choice</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\oplus ]]></fr:tex> with unit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {0}]]></fr:tex>,
and a <html:em>combination</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\otimes ]]></fr:tex> with unit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {1}]]></fr:tex>,
distributing over choice and annihilated by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {0}]]></fr:tex>. Idempotent
choice induces an order,
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[x \sqsubseteq  y \iff  x \oplus  y = x,]]></fr:tex>
under which <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\oplus ]]></fr:tex> is the meet and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {0}]]></fr:tex> the top element.</html:p>
    <html:p>It is <html:em>selective</html:em> when choice always takes one of its
arguments:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[x \oplus  y = x
   \quad \text {or}\quad 
   x \oplus  y = y.]]></fr:tex>
Selectivity is what makes optima <html:em>witnessed</html:em>: a value assembled by
repeated choice is literally one of the candidates offered, so a
certificate for the chosen candidate is a certificate for the
result.</html:p>
    <html:p>For <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G5/" title="Shortest paths by Löb induction" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G5/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G5/" type="local">shortest paths</fr:link>, read <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\oplus ]]></fr:tex> as "take the better
route", <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\otimes ]]></fr:tex> as "extend a route by an edge", <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {0}]]></fr:tex> as
unreachable and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {1}]]></fr:tex> as the free route. Min-plus on costs
gives shortest distances; the Boolean semiring (or, and) gives
reachability.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
